Aug 16 2007	Okay for what it is.	I've stayed at this hotel every August for the past 6 years for a 3-day convention. On the plus side, it's nice to have a slightly larger room with a sofa couch -- in the doubles, three people can stay and each have their own bed. Having the Outback (a regular Outback, not a hotel restaurant) is a godsend if you need to stay onsite for dinner (and I usually do). The refrigerator and microwave in the room are very nice.The breakfast has some variety (fresh waffles, make your own McMuffins) but the breakfast area can be unpleasantly crowded if the hotel is really full. Nearby options for lunch are limited. There is a supermarket about half a mile away, and an L station a bit further.The shuttle from O'Hare seems to work fairly smoothly. It can be a godawful hike through the airport to the shuttle pick-up, but that isn't the hotel's fault. The wi-fi finally worked well and consistently in the guest rooms this year. In previous years, you had to take your laptop into the common area for it to work decently, so yay for that improvement.Our group gets a reasonable rate, but if you want to stay extra days off the group rate, it can be almost 2/3 more per night. On the downside, the rooms are old at this point and need refurbishment. They are almost uniformly dark and the lighting in the vanity area is just awful if you're putting on makeup. The idea of VCR's is nice, but seriously, isn't it time to change to DVD players? It isn't as if they're expensive anymore. (The presence of the VCR's with unputs does make it easy to hook up your own DVD player, if you bring one.) The bed I slept on this time was quite uncomfortable. Also, the extra blanket for the sofa bed was downright skanky -- a dirty foam thing.I've always stayed in the summer, and this year it was really hot. The temperature in the rooms varies between too warm and too cold -- it really is hard to find a happy medium. Unlike most leisure travellers, as I'm there for a meeting, I barely leave the hotel for most of my trip. Overall, this is an okay place to stay, but nothing special. It's kind of a shame -- with a few fairly commonplace upgrades, it could be a really nice, airport convenient and inexpensive hotel.	
