Dec 6 2006 	Really great Hotel	We stayed here for four nights from Dec. 1 - 5, 2006. There were three of us - myself, my 18 year old daughter, and her 19 year old boyfriend. Because of his limited expenses, we chose this hotel due to the free breakfast and the space of the room. I booked a &quot;VIP&quot; suite (corner room, larger than other rooms) at $109 per night. Plenty of room, well appointed, 1/2 size refrigerator and microwave in kitchen area. The breakfast was exactly the same as what you get at the Hampton Inns - warm, sufficient, tasty and filling.The Blue line train ran directly past our room and we faced the airport. We NEVER heard any noise from either. The hotel seems to be fairly new. The decor is nice (retro 30's and 40's airline pictures everywhere), the tiles, walls, etc. remind me of the &quot;Starbucks&quot; decor so popular now.We rode the blue line into and from the city every day. The hotel offers a courtesy shuttle to and from O'Hare - departs the hotel on the top and half of each hour, and picks up at the airport at the quarter past and quarter till of each hour. We used the service 6 times - never once was it late.Total time transport from the hotel to stepping out of the train stop onto State and Washington Avenue - about 1 hour.The hotel offers on the ninth floor a guest laundry (3 washers, 4 dryers, $1 each). The front desk will give you complimentary laundry detergent, fabric softner and dryer sheets for the machines.There is an Outback Steakhouse attached to the hotel and you can access it from the lobby.For our purposes, at $109 per night, this hotel was great, great, great! Everyone was hospitable and the rooms were very clean and comfortable. I would stay here again, definitely!	
